signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Passers with this ability have faster passing animations when they are throwing under pressure
Passers with this ability have perfect accuracy on all cross-body throws up to 20 yards (except on high/low throws).
Passers with this ability receive better pass blocking from their offensive linemen.
Blockers with this ability reduce a rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move while run blocking.
Blockers with this ability will dominantly win impact blocks on screen plays
Players with this ability can detect user-controlled defenders before the snap; as well as 3rd and 4th down blitzers. Can be bluffed.
Players with this ability grant improved blocking to the entire offensive line.
Defenders with this ability can apply pressure to the quarterback from a greater distance.
Defenders with this ability will receive dominant bull rush wins when their pass rush points are full
Defenders with this ability use faster run shed moves for a better chance at shedding blocks against inside run plays.
Zone Hawk defenders lock down a part of the field. When they enter the zone, this ability increases the rate of interceptions while in zone coverage.
Players with this ability are more likely to succeed at and attempt diving catches and swats.
Defenders with this ability have higher chance to catch uncontested interceptions, and they have unlimited stamina on the return (until using a special move or breaking a tackle).
Defenders with this ability generally react much faster to receiver cut moves when in man coverage
Players with this ability will recover from the effects of fatigue at an increased rate between plays.
Ballcarriers with this ability can quickly shift momentum, change direction, and turn the corner without sacrificing speed.
Ballcarriers with this ability will frequently attempt to gain extra yards while being tackled
After securing a RAC catch, ballcarriers with this ability can quickly shift momentum, change direction, and turn the corner without sacrificing speed.
Players with this ability will distract defenders for longer with their runoffs
Receivers with this ability have a high success rate when creating separation on the last cut of any route.
After securing a RAC catch, ballcarriers with this ability can quickly shift momentum, change direction, and turn the corner without sacrificing speed.
Ballcarriers with this ability will break almost any hit-stick tackle attempts made on them.
Ballcarriers with this ability retain more of their forward momentum during tackles while travelling at high speeds.
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS, outside the numbers
